      "chat": "# Chat Transcript - CASE-00001\n\nSynthetic artifact for mock Customer Service Case Resolution Copilot testing.\n\nCustomer: Jordan Reed (CUST-00012)\nChannel: email\nCategory: overdraft fee reversal\n\nCustomer: Hi, I need help with my account ending in ****7148.\nAgent N. Brooks: I can help. I will first verify the profile and then review what happened.\nCustomer: The issue is about overdraft fee reversal. I noticed it after the transaction REF0000071989.\nAgent N. Brooks: I see the related item listed as \"Bill Pay - FastShip\" for $740.54, status Posted.\nCustomer: What can you do today?\nAgent N. Brooks: I will follow the Fee Reversal Playbook and document the next step: Apply courtesy credit when eligible; otherwise explain policy and alternatives.\n\nNo real customer data is present in this transcript.\n",
      "email": "# Email Thread - CASE-00001\n\nFrom: jordan.reed.00012@example.test\nTo: support@berryruth-bank.test\nSubject: Help requested - overdraft fee reversal\n\nHello,\n\nI am writing about account ****7148. The case relates to overdraft fee reversal.\nPlease review reference REF0000071989. I prefer contact by chat.\n\nReply from BerryRuth Bank Support:\n\nThank you for contacting us. We have opened CASE-00001. For your protection, we will not ask for your full account number by email. Our next step is: Apply courtesy credit when eligible; otherwise explain policy and alternatives.\n",
      "callNotes": "# Call Notes - CASE-00001\n\n- Caller verified using synthetic profile challenge.\n- Customer sentiment: Neutral.\n- Stated concern: Customer requests an overdraft fee refund after a timing or courtesy issue.\n- Account reviewed: Credit Card ****7148.\n- Related transaction: TXN-0000373 / Bill Pay - FastShip / Posted.\n- Agent action: Pending copilot recommendation.\n- Follow-up window: 2-3 business days.\n",
      "caseNotes": "# Case Notes - CASE-00001\n\n## Summary\nCustomer requests an overdraft fee refund after a timing or courtesy issue.\n\n## Evidence\n- Customer: CUST-00012\n- Account: ACCT-000212\n- Transaction: TXN-0000373\n- KB article: KB-0001\n\n## Copilot Guidance\nApply courtesy credit when eligible; otherwise explain policy and alternatives.\n\n## Guardrails\n- Do not reveal internal risk notes.\n- Do not guarantee outcomes before required operations team review.\n- Keep all identifiers masked in customer-facing responses.\n",
      "statement": "# Statement Snippet - CASE-00001\n\nAccount: Credit Card ****7148\nStatement period: 2026-05-22 to 2026-06-21\n\n| Date | Description | Amount | Status | Reference |\n|---|---:|---:|---|---|\n| 2026-03-27 | Bill Pay - FastShip | -740.54 | Posted | REF0000071989 |\n| 2026-06-17 | Balance update | 3287.84 | Posted | BAL0212 |\n\nThis statement snippet is synthetic and abbreviated for retrieval tests.\n",
      "responseTemplate": "# Agent Response Template - CASE-00001\n\nHi Jordan,\n\nThanks for contacting us about overdraft fee reversal. I reviewed the case details for your account ending in ****7148 and the related reference REF0000071989.\n\nBased on our Fee Reversal Playbook, the next step is: Apply courtesy credit when eligible; otherwise explain policy and alternatives.\n\nFor your security, please do not send full account numbers, passwords, one-time codes, or full card numbers in this conversation.\n\nThank you,\nBerryRuth Bank Support\n",
