    "KB-0019": "# Fee Reversal Playbook Addendum\n\nArticle ID: KB-0019\nCategory: overdraft fee reversal\nAudience: Frontline Agent\nLast reviewed: 2026-04-22\n\n## Purpose\nCustomer requests an overdraft fee refund after a timing or courtesy issue.\n\n## Agent Procedure\n1. Confirm the customer's identity using approved synthetic verification steps.\n2. Review account status, case history, and related transactions.\n3. Apply the category policy: Apply courtesy credit when eligible; otherwise explain policy and alternatives.\n4. Document the decision, evidence, and any handoff queue.\n\n## Customer-Safe Language\nUse plain language. Acknowledge the concern. Explain the next step without promising outcomes that require operations review.\n\n## Escalation\nEscalate to Deposits Servicing when documentation is incomplete, customer sentiment is high-risk, or the request exceeds frontline authority.\n\nSynthetic article for testing only.\n",
    "KB-0020": "# Debit Card Replacement Procedure Addendum\n\nArticle ID: KB-0020\nCategory: card replacement\nAudience: Supervisor\nLast reviewed: 2026-04-19\n\n## Purpose\nCustomer needs a replacement card due to loss, damage, expiration, or suspected compromise.\n\n## Agent Procedure\n1. Confirm the customer's identity using approved synthetic verification steps.\n2. Review account status, case history, and related transactions.\n3. Apply the category policy: Verify identity, block old card when needed, confirm delivery address and shipping speed.\n4. Document the decision, evidence, and any handoff queue.\n\n## Customer-Safe Language\nUse plain language. Acknowledge the concern. Explain the next step without promising outcomes that require operations review.\n\n## Escalation\nEscalate to Cards Operations when documentation is incomplete, customer sentiment is high-risk, or the request exceeds frontline authority.\n\nSynthetic article for testing only.\n",
    "KB-0021": "# Address Change Verification Standard Addendum\n\nArticle ID: KB-0021\nCategory: address change\nAudience: Frontline Agent\nLast reviewed: 2026-04-16\n\n## Purpose\nCustomer asks to update mailing or residential address.\n\n## Agent Procedure\n1. Confirm the customer's identity using approved synthetic verification steps.\n2. Review account status, case history, and related transactions.\n3. Apply the category policy: Complete step-up verification and confirm tax-document and card-delivery impacts.\n4. Document the decision, evidence, and any handoff queue.\n\n## Customer-Safe Language\nUse plain language. Acknowledge the concern. Explain the next step without promising outcomes that require operations review.\n\n## Escalation\nEscalate to Customer Maintenance when documentation is incomplete, customer sentiment is high-risk, or the request exceeds frontline authority.\n\nSynthetic article for testing only.\n",
    "KB-0022": "# Missing Payment Research Guide Addendum\n\nArticle ID: KB-0022\nCategory: payment not posted\nAudience: Frontline Agent\nLast reviewed: 2026-04-13\n\n## Purpose\nCustomer says a bill pay, loan, card, or deposit payment has not appeared.\n\n## Agent Procedure\n1. Confirm the customer's identity using approved synthetic verification steps.\n2. Review account status, case history, and related transactions.\n3. Apply the category policy: Collect trace data, check posting windows, and open research if outside SLA.\n4. Document the decision, evidence, and any handoff queue.\n\n## Customer-Safe Language\nUse plain language. Acknowledge the concern. Explain the next step without promising outcomes that require operations review.\n\n## Escalation\nEscalate to Payments Research when documentation is incomplete, customer sentiment is high-risk, or the request exceeds frontline authority.\n\nSynthetic article for testing only.\n",
    "KB-0023": "# Online Access Recovery Guide Addendum\n\nArticle ID: KB-0023\nCategory: account access issue\nAudience: Frontline Agent\nLast reviewed: 2026-04-10\n\n## Purpose\nCustomer cannot sign in, pass MFA, reset password, or access mobile banking.\n\n## Agent Procedure\n1. Confirm the customer's identity using approved synthetic verification steps.\n2. Review account status, case history, and related transactions.\n3. Apply the category policy: Validate identity, unlock profile, reset MFA when appropriate, and warn about scams.\n4. Document the decision, evidence, and any handoff queue.\n\n## Customer-Safe Language\nUse plain language. Acknowledge the concern. Explain the next step without promising outcomes that require operations review.\n\n## Escalation\nEscalate to Digital Support when documentation is incomplete, customer sentiment is high-risk, or the request exceeds frontline authority.\n\nSynthetic article for testing only.\n",
    "KB-0024": "# Wire Transfer FAQ Addendum\n\nArticle ID: KB-0024\nCategory: wire transfer question\nAudience: Frontline Agent\nLast reviewed: 2026-04-07\n\n## Purpose\nCustomer asks about wire status, cutoff, fees, limits, or required details.\n\n## Agent Procedure\n1. Confirm the customer's identity using approved synthetic verification steps.\n2. Review account status, case history, and related transactions.\n3. Apply the category policy: Explain cutoff, fee, status, and escalation path without promising settlement.\n4. Document the decision, evidence, and any handoff queue.\n\n## Customer-Safe Language\nUse plain language. Acknowledge the concern. Explain the next step without promising outcomes that require operations review.\n\n## Escalation\nEscalate to Wire Desk when documentation is incomplete, customer sentiment is high-risk, or the request exceeds frontline authority.\n\nSynthetic article for testing only.\n",
    "KB-0025": "# Loan Payoff Quote Procedure Addendum\n\nArticle ID: KB-0025\nCategory: loan payoff question\nAudience: Supervisor\nLast reviewed: 2026-04-04\n\n## Purpose\nCustomer requests payoff balance, quote expiration, per diem, or lien release timing.\n\n## Agent Procedure\n1. Confirm the customer's identity using approved synthetic verification steps.\n2. Review account status, case history, and related transactions.\n3. Apply the category policy: Generate payoff quote, explain good-through date and acceptable payment methods.\n4. Document the decision, evidence, and any handoff queue.\n\n## Customer-Safe Language\nUse plain language. Acknowledge the concern. Explain the next step without promising outcomes that require operations review.\n\n## Escalation\nEscalate to Loan Servicing when documentation is incomplete, customer sentiment is high-risk, or the request exceeds frontline authority.\n\nSynthetic article for testing only.\n",
